  "description": "Phase 6.9 backfill #174: exercises `persistSession: false` (Phase 3.12). Two-turn flow — turn 0 invokes the `write` tool, turn 1 emits final text — so the in-memory StateAccessor's `previousResponseId` roundtrip is load-bearing for the comparator pass: the turn-1 OR request includes `previous_response_id: resp-18-0` and is canonicalized into the prompt hash; if the in-memory accessor failed to carry the id forward, the emulator would script-miss and the scenario would fail. The companion supplemental test in `scenarios.comparative.test.ts` runs an OR-only inline construction with an explicit `logsRoot` tmpdir and asserts zero filesystem writes (no `session.json` / `request.json` / `response.json` / `state.json`). The Anthropic side has no `persistSession` equivalent on the Claude Agent SDK; the comparator pass on this scenario asserts event-stream + hook-firing-order parity given the OR side runs with in-memory state and the Anthropic side runs with its default subprocess persistence — that asymmetry is structural (see PR #190 body, ambiguity call #1).",
